The White House Office of Intergovernmental Affairs hosted a bipartisan group of senior State government officials from 44 States and 4 territories to discuss the relationship between State and Federal governments. Senior White House officials, including Secretary of Energy Rick Perry and Secretary of Health and Human Services Tom Price, spoke about President Donald J. Trump's tax reform agenda and its potential to provide tax relief and create jobs at the local level. The State officials also met with counterparts in the Office of Intergovernmental Affairs and other White House components to streamline communication and build on progress made to empower State and local leaders.